  "prompt": "What do people in Miami wear in the winter?",
  "response": "In Miami, winters are mild compared to many other parts of the United States. During winter months (December-February), temperatures typically range from the 60s to 70s\u00b0F (15-25\u00b0C). People in Miami usually wear:\n\n1. Light layers\n- Light sweaters\n- Long-sleeved shirts\n- Light jackets or windbreakers\n- Cardigans\n\n2. Casual clothing\n- Jeans\n- Shorts (on warmer days)\n- T-shirts\n- Casual dresses\n\n3. Footwear\n- Sneakers\n- Sandals\n- Comfortable walking shoes\n\n4. Accessories\n- Light scarves\n- Sunglasses\n- Baseball caps or sun hats\n\nMost people do not need heavy winter coats or extreme cold-weather gear. The climate remains relatively warm, allowing for comfortable, lightweight clothing throughout the winter season.",
